1. What is a Method?
A method is a small block of code that performs a specific task.

Example:
void sayHello() {
    System.out.println("Hello");
}

2. Why Do We Use Methods?

To avoid writing the same code again and again

Makes code clean

Helps in debugging

Increases reusability

Divides program into small parts (modular)

3. Method Syntax
returnType methodName(parameters) {
    // code
    return value;   // optional
}

4. Types of Methods
With Parameter + With Return
int add(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}

With Parameter + No Return
void greet(String name) {
    System.out.println("Hello " + name);
}

No Parameter + With Return
int getAge() {
    return 20;
}

No Parameter + No Return
void printInfo() {
    System.out.println("Info");
}

5. How to Call a Method
In the same class:
sayHello();

From another class:
A obj = new A();
obj.sayHello();

6. Method Overloading

Same method name, different parameters.

✔ Happens in the same class
✔ Compile-time polymorphism

Example:

int area(int side) {
    return side * side;
}

int area(int length, int breadth) {
    return length * breadth;
}

7. Method Overriding

Child class replaces the parent's method.

Rules:

Same name

Same parameters

Different class

Inheritance required

Example:

class A {
    void show() { System.out.println("A"); }
}

class B extends A {
    @Override
    void show() { System.out.println("B"); }
}

8. Static Methods

A static method can be called without creating an object.

static void msg() {
    System.out.println("Hello");
}


Call:

ClassName.msg();

9. Access Modifiers
Modifier	Meaning
public	Accessible everywhere
private	Only within same class
protected	Same package + subclasses
default	Same package only

Quick Revision Notes:

Method = reusable block of code

void = no return value

Overloading = same name, different parameters

Overriding = same name, same parameters, child class changes method

Static method = called with class name

Recursion = method calling itself